===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Evolved geometrically from {{l|och|胄}} in Han dynasty era ({{zh-ref|Liu, 2023}}).

Before that, Pronunciation 1 was written as {{l|mul|毓}}; see there for more.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}} compares {{cog|kac|tr=lu³¹|t=to give birth (to a child)}}, based on Zhengzhang's Old Chinese reconstruction; however, Baxter and Sagart's reconstruction makes a connection doubtful. For the B-S reconstruction, note similarities to {{cog|my|မွေး|t=to give birth, raise}}.

